The paper discusses a practical solution for runtime verification of distributed, object-oriented applications, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The use of active object framework PROACTIVE suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) as well. The paper also mentions the use of property specifications and monitors, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses blame assignment, which is related to logic (cs.LO).
